array.note: e[k][l] is 1 if the edge in the intermediate cell at coordinates (k,l) is an upward downward, 0 if a downward diagonal
x[i][j] is the number of connected nodes (effective neighbors, or bridges) to node (i,j)
d[i][j] is the distance of node (i,j) from the root to the chain/tree it belongs
aux_gb[i] is the ith auxiliary variable having been automatically introduced

group.note: isolated nodes are roots (are a distance 0)
nodes with at least two neighbors cannot be roots (be at distance 0)
nodes with at least two neighbors have exactly one parent (a node with the same distance minus 1)
the distance between any two neighbors is always 1
